Due to its location within the Umami Kofun Cluster, the park contains numerous ancient Kofuns. Admission is free, and parking is also free. Parking lots open at 8:00 AM year-round, with closing times varying: 6:00 PM during regular seasons, 7:00 PM in summer (June–August), and 5:00 PM in winter (November–February). There are 822 parking spaces available, including temporary lots, though the park is often busy on weekends, leading to full lots.
== Park Facilities == === Nagomi Path (Greenway Area) === * Northern entrance : Adjacent to {{ill|Ikebe Station|ja|池部駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Kintetsu Tawaramoto Line|ja|近鉄田原本線|12=draft|12=draft}}. * Greenway trails * Observation Hill * Mameyama Bridge * Sanbou Bridge 1 * Yamamomo Plaza * Sanbou Bridge 2 * Sanbou Bridge 3 * Sannoya Bridge * Oonozawa Bridge * Murasakishikibu Plaza * Hanaemi Bridge : Connector to the North Area.
=== North Area === The {{ill|Nara Prefectural Route 14|ja|奈良県道14号桜井田原本王寺線|12=draft|12=draft}} runs through the center of this area. The North Area, unlike the Central and South Areas, features large lawns, wooden playground equipment, and sandpits, making it popular with families. * Northern entrance : Centrally located with the North parking lot (240 spaces), temporary parking lot (60 spaces), toilets, and smoking areas. * Ikegami Kofun * Maeike Pond * Large playground * Toshō Pond - Fountain * Sandpit * Western entrance * Large tent - Used for events, including music stages. * Gathering Hill (Large Lawn Plaza) * Umami Flower Garden - A 5,000 m² flower bed showcasing seasonal flowers. * Hanami Teahouse * Café and restaurant * Aya Plaza (Dahlia Garden) - Features sunflowers in summer and dahlias and cosmos in autumn.
=== Central Area === [[File:nagare_tomb_kubire.JPG|thumb|200px|The restored central constriction of Nagareyama Kofun.]] This area is the core of the park, featuring historical sites such as the {{ill|Nagareyama Kofun|ja|ナガレ山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Otomoyama Kofun|ja|乙女山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, along with rose, iris, hydrangea gardens, and a water lily pond. A bus stop is located in the Central Parking Lot, serviced by buses from {{ill|Goidō Station|ja|五位堂駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Kintetsu Osaka Line|ja|近鉄大阪線|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* Visitor Center : A two-story building showcasing the park's kofun and nature through exhibits. The second floor serves as an observation deck. Adjacent to the center is a parking lot with 204 spaces, with additional lots offering 79 and 143 spaces, respectively. : Open 9:00 AM–5:00 PM; closed Mondays (or the following weekday if Monday is a holiday). * Central entrance * Fields and gardens (e.g., Rose Garden, Hydrangea Garden) * Several Kofuns, including {{ill|Nagareyama Kofun|ja|ナガレ山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Otomoyama Kofun|ja|乙女山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}
=== South Area === The southernmost area connects to the Central Area via bridges, including Funkan Bridge and Kitsunezuka Bridge. The area borders the {{ill|Suyama Kofun|ja|巣山古墳|1=Suyama Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kōryō Town Taketori Park|ja|広陵町立竹取公園|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Access == === Public transport === * **Greenway North Entrance**: 2-minute walk from {{ill|Ikebe Station|ja|池部駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the Kintetsu Tawaramoto Line. * **Central Entrance**: Bus services from {{ill|Goidō Station|ja|五位堂駅|12=draft|12=draft}} or community wagons offer access to this area. * **Central South Entrance**: Bus stop near the {{ill|Takatori Park East|ja|竹取公園東|12=draft|12=draft}} stop, a 5-minute walk away.
=== By car === * Approximately 4 km south from the {{ill|Hōryūji Interchange|ja|法隆寺インターチェンジ|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Nishi-Meihan Expressway|ja|西名阪自動車道|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * The {{ill|27th National Urban Greening Fair|ja|全国都市緑化フェア|12=draft|12=draft}} was held here in 2010. * The annual Umami Tulip Fair, starting in 2014, attracts visitors with its vibrant displays.
== Nearby Attractions == * {{ill|Takatori Park|ja|竹取公園|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kōryō Town Library|ja|広陵町立図書館|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Sanuki Shrine|ja|讃岐神社|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kawai Sports Park|ja|河合町総合スポーツ公園|12=draft|12=draft}} * Shinmokuyama Kofun
